 and Jason McCoy, both students, brought stolen guns to school, where they killed principal Richard Allen and injured an assistant principal and an assistant physical education teacher. Harless was shot and wounded by police and McCoy was arrested without injury. Both served prison terms.<ref>[https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=pMUMAAAAIBAJ&sjid=J2EDAAAAIBAJ&pg=6178,5476026&dq= Student was treated at mental hospital], ''[[St. Petersburg Times]]'' (February 13, 1988)</ref>\n|-\n| November 22, 1988\n| [[Abilene, Texas]], United States\n| Mason Staggs, 16\n| \n| 1 injured\n| Mason Staggs, 16, shot Cooper High School teacher Rick Maloney in the face with a derringer, severely injuring him. Staggs then left the school and went fishing.<ref>{{cite news |newspaper=[[Abilene Reporter-News]] |url=http://www.texnews.com/local97/staggs021497.html |title=Mason Staggs denied double jeopardy claim |date=February 14, 1997 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20050320190338/http://www.texnews.com/local97/staggs021497.html |archivedate=March 20, 2005 }}</ref>\n|-\n| December 16, 1988\n| [[Virginia Beach, Virginia]], United States\n| Nicholas Elliott, 16\n| 1 dead\n| 1 injured\n| Nicholas Elliott came to Atlantic Shores Christian School with a firearm bought by an adult relative. He shot two teachers, one fatally, before entering a portable classroom full of students. The gun jammed and Elliott was tackled. Elliott complained of being teased and bullied, Elliott was later sentenced to life in prison in 1989.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.lorrainewakeland.com/pdfarchive/jammed_gun.pdf |title=Jammed gun holds toll to 1 dead; student held |format=PDF |accessdate=2011-03-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110713232358/http://www.lorrainewakeland.com/pdfarchive/jammed_gun.pdf |archive-date=2011-07-13 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=5oabRaJVmysC&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_summary_r&cad=0 |title=Leonard B