ira]], [[Brazil]]\n| ..., 16\n| 1 dead\n| 2 injured\n| During an argument with his girlfriend's brother a 16-year-old student drew a pistol and began shooting at his high school, hitting three students nearby, one of them fatally.<ref>[https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=fqMKAAAAIBAJ&sjid=IU0DAAAAIBAJ&pg=6853,1293079&dq= School shootings raise questions in Brazil], ''The Daily Courier'' (March 11, 2001)</ref>\n|-\n| March 7, 2001\n| [[Williamsport, Pennsylvania]], United States\n| Elizabeth C. Bush, 14\n|\n| 1 injured\n| Elizabeth Bush shoots and injures Kimberly Marchese at Bishop Neumann High School.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_m1141/is_25_37/ai_73827824/ |title=Girl sentenced in school shooting |publisher=Findarticles.com |date=2001-04-20 |accessdate=2011-03-12 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111022005429/http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_m1141/is_25_37/ai_73827824/ |archivedate=2011-10-22 }}</ref>\n|-\n| March 22, 2001\n| [[El Cajon, California]], United States\n| Jason Hoffman, 18\n|\n| 5 injured\n| 18-year-old student Jason Hoffman opened fire with a handgun and shotgun at [[Granite Hills High School (El Cajon, California)|Granite Hills High School]], in [[El Cajon, California]], wounding three students and two teachers. Hoffman committed suicide in prison in 2002.<ref>{{cite news|title=Witnesses Recall School Rampage|url=https://articles.latimes.com/2001/may/11/local/me-62286|newspaper=LA Times|date=May 11, 2001|first=Tony|last=Perry}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Granite Hills gunman's kin file claim vs. county, sheriff|url=http://legacy.utsandiego.com/news/metro/granitehills/20020510-9999_2m10jason.html|newspaper=LA Times|date=May 10, 2002|access-date=June 26, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131224122239/http://legacy.utsandiego.com/news/metro/granitehills/20020510-9999_2m10jason.html|archive-date=December 24, 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n|-\n| March 26, 2001\n| [[Machakos]], [[Kenya]]\n| Felix Mambo Ngumbao, 16, and Davies Otieno Onyango, 17\n| 67 dead\n| 19 injured\n| [[Kyanguli Fire Tragedy]]: Two students set fire to a dormitory at Kyanguli Secondary School located in Machakos, {{convert|30|mi|km}} southeast of [[Nairobi]], after the final exam results were annulled and payment of their outstanding school fees was demanded. 67 people perished in the flames and another 19 were injured, including one of the perpetrators.<ref>[http://www.dispatch.co.za/2001/04/10/foreign/GKENYAN.HTM Pupils appear for Kenyan school fire] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20041107131352/http://www.dispatch.co.za/2001/04/10/foreign/GKENYAN.HTM |date=2004-11-07 }}, ''[[Daily Dispatch]]'' (April 10, 2001)</ref><ref>[http://www.wsws.org/articles/2001/mar2001/keny-m30.shtml Kenya: School fire kills at least 59 students], ''[[World Socialist Web Site]]'' (March 30, 2001)</ref>\n|-\n| March 30, 2001\n| [[Gary, Indiana]], United States\n| Donald Ray Burt Jr., 17\n| 1 dead\n|\n| Donald Ray Burt Jr., a 17-year-old expelled student, shot and killed 16-year-old student Neal Boyd III in the parking lot of [[Lew Wallace High School]], in [[Gary, Indiana]], Burt Jr. was sentenced to 57 years in prison on July 25, 2002.<ref>{{cite web|title=School Safety Interim Study Committee |url=http://www.in.gov/legislative/interim/committee/minutes/SSICG9O.pdf|publisher=Indiana.gov|date=September 24, 2013}}</ref>\n|-\n| August 6, 2001\n| [[Maca\u00fabas]], [[Bahia]], Brazil\n| Rob\u00e9rio Souza de Oliveira, 18\n| 1 dead\n| 7 injured\n| Rob\u00e9rio Souza de Oliveira, an 18-year-old farmer, shot and wounded six students and a teacher with a shotgun at Escola Estadual Alo\u00edsio Short. He then commmitted suicide by shooting himself in the head.<ref>[http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/folha/cotidiano/ult95u34424.shtml Agricultor de 18 anos invade escola na Bahia, fere 7 \u00e0 bala e se suicida], ''[[Folha de S.Paulo]]'' (August 6, 2001)</ref><ref>[http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fsp