/trials/taped/clinard/background_ctv.html?page=1 |title=Jason Clinard, 14 sentenced to life imprisonment for school bus driver killing |publisher=Courttv.com |accessdate=2011-03-12 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080202054719/http://www.courttv.com/trials/taped/clinard/background_ctv.html?page=1 |archivedate=2008-02-02 }}</ref>\n|-\n| March 21, 2005\n| [[Red Lake, Minnesota]], United States\n| [[Jeffrey Weise]], 16\n| 10 dead\n| 12+ injured\n| [[Red Lake shootings]]. Jeffrey Weise, a student at Red Lake High School in Red Lake, Minnesota, killed his grandfather and his grandfather's girlfriend before killing seven more people: five students, a teacher, and an unarmed security guard at Red Lake High School. The attack concluded when Weise exchanged fire with police, and then retreated to a classroom where he fatally shot himself.\n|-\n| June 10, 2005\n| [[Hikari, Yamaguchi]], Japan\n| ..., 18\n|\n| 58 injured\n| An 18-year-old student, whose name was not disclosed, threw a homemade bomb into a classroom at Hikari Senior High School, injuring 58 people, most of them slightly. The perpetrator later told police that the attack was directed against a group of students who had teased him for his shyness.<ref>[http://www.japantimes.co.jp/weekly/news/nn2005/nn20050618a1.htm Indiscriminate bomb targets student], ''[[The Japan Times]]'' (June 18, 2005)</ref>\n|-\n| September 9, 2005\n| [[Bangkok]], [[Thailand]]\n| Jitrada Tantiwanichayasuk, 34\n|\n| 4 injured\n| Jitrada Tantiwanichayasuk, a mentally disturbed woman, stabbed four girls at Saint Joseph Convent School in Bangkok, before escaping on a motorcycle. She was later arrested and sentenced to four years in prison.<ref>[http://www.nationmultimedia.com/2005/09/09/headlines/data/headlines_18562307.html St Joseph Convent School turmoil: Parents shocked, four students stabbed] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121010052038/http://www.nationmultimedia.com/2005/09/09/headlines/data/headlines_18562307.html |date=2012-10-10 }}, ''[[The Nation (Thailand)|The Nation]]'' (September 9, 2005)</ref><ref>[http://www.nationmultimedia.com/2008/11/20/national/national_30088912.php Court sentences woman who stabbed students in 2005 to four years in jail] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121010052047/http://www.nationmultimedia.com/2008/11/20/national/national_30088912.php |date=2012-10-10 }}, ''[[The Nation (Thailand)|The Nation]]'' (November 20, 2008)</ref>\n|-\n| September 13, 2005\n| [[Chicago]], [[Illinois]], United States\n| ..., 15\n|\n| 1 injured\n| At [[Harlan Community Academy High School]], a fight broke between two 15-year-old boys in the gymnasium. One of the boys took out a .25-caliber pistol and shot the other one in the leg. A police officer on duty at the school arrested the gunman. The suspected shooter was charged as an adult with aggravated battery with a firearm.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.chicagotribune.com/2005-09-15/news/0509150337_1_school-shooting-gym-bond-hearing |title=Teen held in school shooting|date=September 15, 2005 |accessdate=September 4, 2013|newspaper=[[Chicago Tribune]]}}</ref>\n|-\n| September 15, 2005\n| [[Vienna]], Austria\n| ..., 15\n| 1 dead\n|\n| During a scuffle a student stabbed and killed a 14-year-old schoolmate at a Vienna school. He was sentenced to seven years in prison.<ref>[http://www.wienerzeitung.at/DesktopDefault.aspx?TabID=3940&Alias=wzo&cob=216352 Sieben Jahre Haft f\u00fcr Sch\u00fclermord], ''[[Wiener Zeitung]]'' (January 27, 2006)</ref>\n|-\n| November 8, 2005\n| [[Jacksboro, Tennessee]], United States\n| Kenneth Bartley, Jr., 14\n| 1 dead\n| 2 injured\n| [[Campbell County High School shooting]]. After being confronted about bringing a gun on school property, 14-year-old Kenneth Bartley opened fire on three school administrators at [[Campbell County High School (Tennessee)|Campbell County High School]], killing assistant principal Ken Bruce and critically wounding the principal and another assistant principal. The shooting was not premeditated.\n|-\n| January 13, 2006\n| [[Longwood, Florida]], [[Florida]], United States\n| Christopher David Penley, 15\n| 1 dead\n|\n| 15-year-old Christopher Penley held his classroom at Milwee Middle School, in [[Longwood, Florida]], [[Florida]] at gunpoint and holed himself in a restroom [[alcove (architecture)|alcove]], holding law enforcement at bay. He was eventually shot by a [[SWAT]] member, after raising the weapon at an officer. The weapon was a pellet gun.<ref name=ctvlist>{{cite news|title=List of major incidents at North American schools|work=[[Canadian Press]]|publisher=[[CTV television network|CTV.ca]]|date=2006-09-13|url=http://www.ctv.ca/servlet/ArticleNews/story/CTVNews/20060913/violence_timeline_060913/20060913/|accessdate=2006-09-14}}</ref>\n|-\n| February 23, 2006\n| [[Roseburg, Oregon]], United States\n| Vincent Wayne Leodoro, 14\n|\n| 1 injured\n| 14-year-old Vincent Leodoro shot 16-year-old fellow student Joseph Monti in the back four times with a [[10mm]] [[semi-automatic pistol]], critically injuring him, in the courtyard of [[Roseburg High School]] in [[Roseburg, Oregon]]. He was found guilty of attempted murder and assault in July 2006, and will be held in prison until he turns 25 years old.<ref>{{cite web|title=Teen found guilty in Roseburg High shooting|url=http://www.katu.com/news/3633746.html|publisher=KATU|date=June 29, 2006|accessdate=February 1, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Teenager faces charges in Oregon high school shooting\n|url=http://seattletimes.com/html/localnews/2002826654_weboreshooting24.html|newspaper=Seattle Times|date=February 24, 2006|accessdate=February 1, 2013}}</ref>\n|-\n| March 14, 2006\n| [[Reno]], [[Nevada]], United States\n| James Scott Newman, 14\n|\n| 2 injured\n| [[Pine Middle School shooting]]. 14-year-old student James Newman brought a [[.38 ACP|.38-caliber]] [[revolver]] to Pine Middle School in [[Reno]], [[Nevada]], and shot and injured two students at random in the school's hallway before being restrained by a physical education teacher.<ref name=\"KOLOTV\">{{cite news\n|first = Koula\n|last = Gianulias\n|author2=Kara Tsuboi |author3=Ed Pearce\n |title = Reno School Shooting Team Report\n|url = http://www.kolotv.com/home/headlines/2461261.html\n|work=\n|publisher= [[KOLO-TV]]\n|location = [[Reno, Nevada]], United States\n|accessdate = 2008-11-21\n }}</ref><ref name=\"LasVegasReview\">{{cite news\n|first = Sandra\n|last = Chereb\n|author2=Kara Tsuboi |author3=Ed Pearce\n |title = School shooting arraignment delayed in school\n|url = http://www.reviewjournal.com/lvrj_home/2006/Mar-18-Sat-2006/news/6431035.html\n|agency = [[The Associated Press]]\n|work= [[Las Vegas Review-Journal]]\n|publisher= Sherman Frederick\n|location = [[Las Vegas, Nevada]], United States\n|date = 2006-03-18\n|accessdate = 2008-11-21\n|quote =\n }}</ref> Newman was charged as a juvenile for two counts of [[Battery (crime)|battery]] with a deadly weapon and was sentenced to [[house arrest]] and 200 hours of [[community service]].<ref name=\"WashingtonPost\">{{cite news\n|first = Scott\n|last = Sonner\n|title = Teen Gets House Arrest in Nev. Shooting\n|url = https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2006/05/26/AR2006052602039_Technorati.html\n|work= [[The Washington Post]]\n|publisher= [[Katharine Weymouth]]\n|location = Washington, D.C., United States\n|date = 2006-05-26\n|accessdate = 2008-11-21\n|quote =\n }}</ref>\n|-\n| June 6, 2006\n| [[Los Angeles, California]], United States\n|\n| 1 dead\n|\n| 17-year-old Venice High School junior Augustine Contreras was shot and killed in one of the school's parking lots shortly after the day's classes ended. He was shot after he went to the aid of his brothers, who were involved in a fight with several other young men. The fight was reportedly stemmed from a local gang dispute between Latino and black students. Two arrests were made but the suspects were released shortly thereafter.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/latimes/access/1049088491.html?dids=1049088491:1049088491&FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&type=current&date=Jun+06%2C+2006&author=Amanda+Covarrubias+and+Lynn+Doan&pub=Los+Angeles+Times&desc=Student+Fatally+Shot+at+Venice+High%3B+The+17-year-old+was+killed+after+a+campus+fistfight+involving+Latinos+and+blacks.+Some+fear+a+resumption+of+gang+violence.&pqatl=google |title=Student Fatally Shot at Venice High; The 17-year-old was killed after a campus fistfight involving Latinos and blacks. Some fear a resumption of gang violence |publisher=Pqasb.pqarchiver.com |date=2006-06-06 |accessdate=2011-03-12 |first1=Amanda |last1=Covarrubias |first2=Lynn |last2=Doan}}</ref>\n|-\n| August 30, 2006\n| [[Hillsborough, North Carolina]], United States\n| Alvaro Rafael Castillo, 19\n| 1 dead\n| 2 injured\n| 19-year-old Alvaro Rafael Castillo opened fire at Orange High School with a rifle and shotgun, shooting eight times and wounding two students. Officers ordered him to stop firing and he immediately complied. Castillo killed his father with a firearm before driving to school in a van. In the van police officers found ammunition, pipe bombs, and other weapons.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://usatoday30.usatoday.com/news/nation/2006-08-31-school-shooting_x.htm |work=USA Today | title=North Carolina Shooting Suspect Obsessed with Columbine | date=August 31, 2006}}</ref><ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2006/08/31/AR2006083100240_pf.html |work=USA Today | title=Shooting Suspect Obsessed with Columbine | date=August 31, 2006}}</ref>\n|-\n| September 27, 2006\n| [[Bailey, Colorado]], United States\n| [[Duane Morrison]], 53\n| 2 dead\n| 6 injured <!-- Injury: Sexual assault -->\n| A gunman, later identified as 53-year-old Duane Morrison of Denver, took six female students hostage at [[Platte Canyon High School]]. After sexually assaulting some of them, he released four of the hostages. When 16-year-old [[Emily Keyes]] tried to run away, Morrison shot her in the back of the head before killing himself. Keyes was flown to St. Anthony Central Hospital in Denver, where she died a short time later.\n|-\n| September 29, 2006\n| [[Cazenovia, Wisconsin]], United States\n| [[Eric Hainstock]], 15\n| 1 dead\n|\n| Eric Hainstock, 15, a freshman at [[Weston High School (Wisconsin)|Weston High School]], brought a shotgun and a handgun to school and confronted the principal. The shotgun was wrestled away from him, but in a struggle over the handgun Hainstock shot the principal, who died later of his wounds. Hainstock had complained that the principal and teachers had failed to stop homophobic bullying directed at him. He also had recently received discipline for bringing tobacco to school and throwing a stapler at a teacher. Hainstock suffered from long term ADHD and abusive treatment at home. He was tried as an adult and sentenced to life in prison.\n|-\n| October 9, 2006\n| [[Joplin, Missouri]], United States\n| Thomas White, 13\n|\n|\n| A 13-year-old student fired a cheap imitation [[AK-47]] inside his middle school after confronting two others students and his principal. The student was wearing a mask and had pointed the gun at the principal, the assistant superintendent and two students. After firing a shot into the ceiling and breaking a water pipe, the student's gun jammed when he attempted to fire additional shots. The student was then confronted by police officers and taken into custody. Officers also found a note in the student's backpack indicating that he had placed an explosive in the school (which has 700 students). No one was injured in the incident. White was sentenced to 10 years in prison. \n|-\n| October 19, 2006\n| [[Orlando, Florida]], United States\n| Kelvin De La Cruz, 17\n| 1 dead\n|\n| 17-year-old Kelvin De La Cruz stabbed 15-year-old Michael Nieves in the chest with a pocket knife at a school bus stop of the Main Campus at University High School. After he stabbed him, Cruz hid under the bus and attempted to change his clothes, but was apprehended and charged with first-degree murder. Nieves died two hours after being stabbed.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cnn.com/2006/US/10/19/highschoolboy.dead/index.html |title=High school boy fatally stabbed at campus bus stop |publisher=Cnn.com |date=2006-10-20 |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| November 20, 2006\n| [[Emsdetten]], Germany\n| Bastian Bosse, 18\n| 1 dead\n| 37 injured\n| [[Emsdetten school shooting]]. An 18-year-old former student entered the Geschwister Scholl school in western Germany with a sawed off shotgun, a 22 caliber rifle, a pistol and a set of explosive devices. The rampage started when Bosse shot and wounded six people with his guns. Police stormed the building, and the shooter released several smoke bombs as he retreated to the third floor, which caused injuries to people inside the school and police officers due to smoke inhalation. The suspect then took his own life.\n|-\n| December 12, 2006\n| [[Erdenheim, Pennsylvania]], United States\n| \n| 1 dead\n| \n| An 11th-grader brought a rifle to school and fired several shots at the ceiling. He then turned the gun on himself and took his own life.<ref>{{cite web|title=Teen Commits Suicide in Hallway of Pennsylvania School|url=http://www.foxnews.com/story/2006/12/12/teen-commits-suicide-in-hallway-pennsylvania-school/|website=Fox News|publisher=Associated Press|accessdate=1 December 2014}}</ref>\n|-\n| January 3, 2007\n| [[Tacoma, Washington]], United States\n| Douglas S. Chanthabouly, 18\n| 1 dead\n|\n| 18-year-old Douglas S. Chanthabouly shot 17-year-old Samnang Kok to death in the [[Henry Foss High School]] hallways due to a personal disagreement. Chathabouly was found guilty of second-degree murder and was sentenced to 23 years of prison.<ref name=\"tacomatrial\">{{cite web | title = Young man convicted in Foss High School shooting sentenced to prison | publisher = The News Tribune | date = June 5, 2009 | url = http://blog.thenewstribune.com/crime/2009/06/05/young-man-convicted-in-foss-high-school-shooting-sentenced-to-prison/ | first = Adam | last = Lynn | accessdate = May 21, 2013 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20140226021748/http://blog.thenewstribune.com/crime/2009/06/05/young-man-convicted-in-foss-high-school-shooting-sentenced-to-prison/ | archive-date = February 26, 2014 | url-status = dead }}</ref>\n|-\n| January 19, 2007\n| [[Sudbury, Massachusetts]], United States\n| John Odgren, 16\n| 1 dead\n|\n| 15-year-old James Alenson was [[n:Stabbing at Massachusetts high school leaves one dead|stabbed to death with a knife in the Lincoln-Sudbury Regional High School washroom]] in the East House section by 16-year-old John Odgren. Odgren did not know Alenson, and he chose to stab him at random. In 2010, Odgren was found guilty of first-degree murder and was sentenced to life without parole.<ref>\"[http://www.metrowestdailynews.com/homepage/8998993118795661308 'I did it ... I did it': Student suspect in deadly stabbing is held without bail]{{dead link|date=May 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}\", ''The MetroWest Daily News'', January 19, 2007. Retrieved January 19, 2007.</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thebostonchannel.com/news/10792195/detail.html |title=Teen Charged In Fellow Student's Death Freshman Stabbed To Death In High School |date=January 19, 2007 |work=WCVB-TV |accessdate=2009-10-18 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090602220401/http://www.thebostonchannel.com/news/10792195/detail.html |archivedate=June 2, 2009 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thebostonchannel.com/news/21313592/detail.html |title=Judge OK's Teen's Jailhouse Tapes In Stab Case Prosecutors Challenging Whether Odgren Was Legally Insane |date=October 16, 2009 |work=WCVB-TV |accessdate=2009-10-18 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091019100830/http://www.thebostonchannel.com/news/21313592/detail.html |a